compared using NEAT with uniform (homogeneous) activation in all neurons to=
 evolving the neurons&#39; activation functions (heterogeneous networks). Neuro=
ns are initialized with a random activation function (picked from a small l=
ist of functions). We introduced a mutation operator that allows mutating t=
he activation function of up to one neuron per individual per generation. W=
e protect innovation by adjusting the innovation number of all incoming and=
 outgoing weights of the mutated neuron.
Three benchmark datasets were used=
 - NEAT was able to create networks that had a testing accuracy similar to =
that of the best homogeneous networks, but the heterogeneous networks that =
were created were much smaller, more parsimonious, reducing the number of w=
